---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Gaming Console Repair | Jake Fixes Tech — Littleton, NH"
description="PlayStation, Xbox, Nintendo Switch, retro consoles and more. Diagnosis, disc drive repair, overheating fixes, cleaning and retro odds and ends. Serving Littleton NH and the North Country.">

  <!-- Header Banner -->
  <section style="position:relative;overflow:hidden;background-color:rgb(30,64,175);">
    <img src="/hero.jpg" alt="Professional tech workspace with dual monitors" fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" style="position:absolute;inset:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;z-index:0;" />
    <div style="position:absolute;inset:0;background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(30,64,175,0.88),rgba(37,99,235,0.88));z-index:1;"></div>
    <div style="max-width:56rem;margin:0 auto;padding:4rem 1.5rem;text-align:center;position:relative;z-index:2;">
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;color:#93c5fd;">
        <a href="/services" style="color:#93c5fd;text-decoration:none;" aria-label="Back to all services">← Services</a>
      </p>
      <h1 style="margin-top:0.75rem;font-size:2.5rem;font-weight:800;color:white;line-height:1.2;">Gaming Console Repair</h1>
      <p style="margin-top:1rem;color:#bfdbfe;line-height:1.75;font-size:1.1rem;max-width:42rem;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;">
        PlayStation, Xbox, Nintendo Switch and more. I diagnose and repair common console issues including disc drives, overheating and general wear and tear — modern and retro.
      </p>
      <div style="margin-top:1.5rem;display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;justify-content:center;gap:1rem;">
        <a href="/contact" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;background:white;color:#1e40af;font-weight:700;padding:0.75rem 1.75rem;border-radius:0.5rem;text-decoration:none;font-size:1rem;">
          Get a Free Quote
          <svg style="height:1rem;width:1rem;" aria-hidden="true" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
        </a>
        <a href="/pricing" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.15);color:white;font-weight:600;padding:0.75rem 1.75rem;border-radius:0.5rem;text-decoration:none;font-size:1rem;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.3);">
          View Pricing
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Info Bar -->
  <section style="background:#1e40af;padding:1.25rem 1.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width:56rem;margin:0 auto;display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;align-items:center;justify-content:center;gap:2rem;text-align:center;">
      <div>
        <div style="font-size:1.75rem;font-weight:800;color:white;">From $60</div>
        <div style="font-size:0.8rem;color:#bfdbfe;font-weight:600;">Diagnostics &amp; Repair</div>
      </div>
      <div style="width:1px;height:2.5rem;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.2);flex-shrink:0;"></div>
      <div>
        <div style="font-size:1.75rem;font-weight:800;color:white;">Free Quote</div>
        <div style="font-size:0.8rem;color:#bfdbfe;font-weight:600;">Honest Assessment</div>
      </div>
      <div style="width:1px;height:2.5rem;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.2);flex-shrink:0;"></div>
      <div>
        <div style="font-size:1.75rem;font-weight:800;color:white;">30 Day</div>
        <div style="font-size:0.8rem;color:#bfdbfe;font-weight:600;">Labor Warranty</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What I Work On -->
  <section style="background:#f8fafc;padding:4rem 1.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width:56rem;margin:0 auto;">
      <div style="margin-bottom:2.5rem;">
        <p style="font-size:0.875rem;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;color:#2563eb;">Consoles I Service</p>
        <h2 style="font-size:2rem;font-weight:800;color:#111827;margin-top:0.5rem;">What I Work On</h2>
        <p style="color:#6b7280;margin-top:0.75rem;line-height:1.75;">From current-gen consoles to retro classics, I can diagnose and repair a wide range of gaming hardware. If you're not sure whether I can help with yours, just ask.</p>
      </div>

      <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1rem;">

        <div class="service-item" style="border-left:4px solid #2563eb;">
          <div class="service-icon" style="background:#dbeafe;color:#2563eb;" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="2" y="6" width="20" height="12" rx="2"/><path d="M6 12h.01M10 12h.01M7 9l-1 3 1 3M13 9l1 3-1 3"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="item-title">PlayStation &amp; Xbox</h3>
            <p class="item-desc">PS4, PS5, Xbox One, Xbox Series X/S and earlier models. Common issues like disc drive failures, overheating, HDMI port issues (where board-level soldering is not required) and general hardware faults. I have experience with optical drive repairs including the chip transfer process required on Xbox One X disc drive swaps.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="service-item" style="border-left:4px solid #7c3aed;">
          <div class="service-icon" style="background:#ede9fe;color:#6d28d9;" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="5" y="2" width="14" height="20" rx="2"/><circle cx="12" cy="17" r="1" fill="currentColor"/><path d="M9 7h6M9 11h6"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="item-title">Nintendo Switch &amp; Switch Lite</h3>
            <p class="item-desc">Joy-Con drift, charging issues, screen damage, general hardware faults and more. The Switch is one of the most repairable modern consoles and many common issues are very fixable. Screen replacement on Switch and Switch Lite is also available.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="service-item" style="border-left:4px solid #15803d;">
          <div class="service-icon" style="background:#dcfce7;color:#15803d;" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M12 2L2 7l10 5 10-5-10-5z"/><path d="M2 17l10 5 10-5"/><path d="M2 12l10 5 10-5"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="item-title">Retro Consoles</h3>
            <p class="item-desc">N64, GameCube, Wii, Wii U and other classic hardware. I enjoy working on retro gear and have hands-on experience with these systems. Whether it's a console that won't power on, a disc drive that won't read, or just needs a good clean, bring it in.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="service-item" style="border-left:4px solid #b45309;">
          <div class="service-icon" style="background:#fef3c7;color:#b45309;" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M14.7 6.3a1 1 0 0 0 0 1.4l1.6 1.6a1 1 0 0 0 1.4 0l3.77-3.77a6 6 0 0 1-7.94 7.94l-6.91 6.91a2.12 2.12 0 0 1-3-3l6.91-6.91a6 6 0 0 1 7.94-7.94l-3.76 3.76z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="item-title">Retro Odds &amp; Ends</h3>
            <p class="item-desc">Game Boy cartridge battery replacements, cleaning corroded contacts, general handheld repairs and other small retro jobs. If you have a quirky retro repair that doesn't fit neatly into a category, describe it and I'll let you know if it's something I can tackle.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Common Repairs -->
  <section style="background:white;padding:4rem 1.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width:56rem;margin:0 auto;">
      <div style="margin-bottom:2.5rem;">
        <p style="font-size:0.875rem;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;color:#2563eb;">Common Issues</p>
        <h2 style="font-size:2rem;font-weight:800;color:#111827;margin-top:0.5rem;">Repairs I Do Regularly</h2>
        <p style="color:#6b7280;margin-top:0.75rem;line-height:1.75;">These are the issues I see most often. If your problem isn't on this list, reach out anyway — this isn't an exhaustive list of everything I can handle.</p>
      </div>

      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill,minmax(15rem,1fr));gap:1rem;">

        <div class="repair-card">
          <div class="repair-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M12 8v4l3 3"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Overheating &amp; Loud Fans</h3>
          <p>Dust buildup is the most common cause of console overheating. A thorough internal clean and fresh thermal paste usually sorts it out.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="repair-card">
          <div class="repair-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="3"/><path d="M19.07 4.93a10 10 0 0 1 0 14.14"/><path d="M4.93 4.93a10 10 0 0 0 0 14.14"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Disc Drive Failures</h3>
          <p>Won't read discs, makes grinding noises, or ejects on its own. Disc drive repair and replacement is one of the more common console repairs I do.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="repair-card">
          <div class="repair-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M18 20V10"/><path d="M12 20V4"/><path d="M6 20v-6"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Joy-Con Drift</h3>
          <p>The analog stick registers movement when you're not touching it. A very common Switch issue with a well-known fix — usually a stick replacement.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="repair-card">
          <div class="repair-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M13 2L3 14h9l-1 8 10-12h-9l1-8z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Won't Power On</h3>
          <p>Dead console, no lights, no response. Diagnosed from the power supply outward — often a fixable issue rather than a dead board.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="repair-card">
          <div class="repair-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="2" y="3" width="20" height="14" rx="2"/><line x1="8" y1="21" x2="16" y2="21"/><line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12" y2="21"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>No Video Output</h3>
          <p>Console powers on but nothing shows on the TV. Can be a cable issue, HDMI handshake problem, or hardware fault — I'll track down the cause.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="repair-card">
          <div class="repair-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M3 6h18M3 12h18M3 18h18"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Internal Cleaning</h3>
          <p>Even if nothing is broken yet, a dusty console runs hotter and louder. Preventive cleaning extends the life of your hardware and keeps it running quietly.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Honest Limitations -->
  <section style="background:#f8fafc;padding:4rem 1.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width:56rem;margin:0 auto;">
      <div style="margin-bottom:2rem;">
        <p style="font-size:0.875rem;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;color:#2563eb;">Honest Limitations</p>
        <h2 style="font-size:2rem;font-weight:800;color:#111827;margin-top:0.5rem;">What I Don't Do</h2>
        <p style="color:#6b7280;margin-top:0.75rem;line-height:1.75;">I'd rather be upfront than take your console in and have to turn it away. Here's where my scope ends.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1rem;">

        <div class="limit-item">
          <div class="limit-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M9 3H5a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v4m6-6h10a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v4M9 3v18m0 0h10a2 2 0 0 0 2-2v-4M9 21H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2v-4m0 0h18"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Complex Board-Level Soldering</h3>
            <p>I can handle straightforward soldering tasks — things like swapping daughter board chips on optical drives. What I don't do is complex motherboard-level work like replacing USB or HDMI ports directly on the board. That requires microscope-level precision and equipment I don't have.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="limit-item">
          <div class="limit-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="5" y="2" width="14" height="20" rx="2"/><line x1="12" y1="18" x2="12.01" y2="18"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Phones &amp; Tablets</h3>
            <p>Not a gaming console service, but worth saying — I don't do phone or tablet screen repairs currently. Those need specialized heat tools I don't have yet.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Not Sure? Just Ask -->
  <section style="background:white;padding:4rem 1.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width:56rem;margin:0 auto;">
      <div style="background:#eff6ff;border:2px solid #bfdbfe;border-radius:0.75rem;padding:2rem;display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:1.5rem;flex-wrap:wrap;">
        <div style="display:flex;height:3rem;width:3rem;min-width:3rem;align-items:center;justify-content:center;border-radius:0.5rem;background:#dbeafe;color:#2563eb;flex-shrink:0;" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M8 9a4 4 0 1 1 4 4v2"/><circle cx="12" cy="19" r="1" fill="currentColor"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div style="flex:1;min-width:200px;">
          <h3 style="font-size:1.1rem;font-weight:700;color:#1e40af;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Not Sure If I Can Help? Just Ask.</h3>
          <p style="color:#1e40af;font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.75;margin:0;">Have a console with an unusual problem, a weird retro repair, or something that doesn't fit the list above? Describe what you've got and what's going on and I'll give you a straight answer on whether I can help.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1e40af,#2563eb);padding:4rem 1.5rem;text-align:center;">
    <div style="max-width:40rem;margin:0 auto;">
      <h2 style="font-size:2rem;font-weight:800;color:white;margin-bottom:1rem;">Console Acting Up?</h2>
      <p style="color:#bfdbfe;font-size:1.1rem;line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:2rem;">Describe what's going on and I'll let you know what it's likely to take to fix it. Free diagnosis, honest advice, no pressure.</p>
      <div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;justify-content:center;gap:1rem;">
        <a href="/contact" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;background:white;color:#2563eb;font-weight:700;padding:0.875rem 2rem;border-radius:0.5rem;text-decoration:none;font-size:1rem;">
          <svg style="height:1.25rem;width:1.25rem;" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 4h16c1.1 0 2 .9 2 2v12c0 1.1-.9 2-2 2H4c-1.1 0-2-.9-2-2V6c0-1.1.9-2 2-2z"/><polyline points="22,6 12,13 2,6"/></svg>
          Get in Touch
        </a>
        <a href="tel:+18022341552" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.15);color:white;font-weight:600;padding:0.875rem 2rem;border-radius:0.5rem;text-decoration:none;font-size:1rem;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.3);">
          <svg style="height:1.25rem;width:1.25rem;" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M22 16.92v3a2 2 0 0 1-2.18 2 19.79 19.79 0 0 1-8.63-3.07A19.5 19.5 0 0 1 4.69 12a19.79 19.79 0 0 1-3.07-8.67A2 2 0 0 1 3.6 1.28h3a2 2 0 0 1 2 1.72c.127.96.361 1.903.7 2.81a2 2 0 0 1-.45 2.11L7.91 8.96a16 16 0 0 0 6.29 6.29l.54-.54a2 2 0 0 1 2.11-.45c.907.339 1.85.573 2.81.7A2 2 0 0 1 21.28 17z"/></svg>
          (802) 234-1552
        </a>
      </div>
      <p style="color:#bfdbfe;font-size:0.875rem;margin-top:1.5rem;">
        <a href="/services" style="color:#bfdbfe;text-decoration:underline;" aria-label="Back to all services">← Back to All Services</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  .service-item {
    background: white;
    border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .service-icon {
    height: 3rem;
    width: 3rem;
    min-width: 3rem;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .service-icon svg {
    height: 1.5rem;
    width: 1.5rem;
  }

  .item-title {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #111827;
    margin-bottom: 0.375rem;
  }

  .item-desc {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #4b5563;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .repair-card {
    background: #f8fafc;
    border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1.25rem;
  }

  .repair-icon {
    display: flex;
    height: 2.5rem;
    width: 2.5rem;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    background: #dbeafe;
    color: #2563eb;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .repair-icon svg {
    height: 1.25rem;
    width: 1.25rem;
  }

  .repair-card h3 {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #111827;
    margin-bottom: 0.375rem;
  }

  .repair-card p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: #6b7280;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .limit-item {
    background: white;
    border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .limit-icon {
    display: flex;
    height: 2.5rem;
    width: 2.5rem;
    min-width: 2.5rem;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    background-color: #dbeafe;
    color: #2563eb;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .limit-icon svg {
    height: 1.25rem;
    width: 1.25rem;
  }

  .limit-item h3 {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #111827;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .limit-item p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: #6b7280;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .service-item {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.75rem;
    }
    .limit-item {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>